   "source": [
    "4. What is the difference between a function and a function call?\n",
    "Ans: A function is a sequence of code we create once and use it later. Function call means after creating a function, we need to call it when we want to use it ."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "4d750c78",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "5. How many global scopes are there in a Python program? How many local scopes?\n",
    "Ans: Only one global scope and it remains until the program terminates.\n",
    "There is only one local scope in python program."
